    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `ColorScheme` autocmd doesn't fire when using `:colorscheme` from the `UIEnter` autocmd.\n\nI set my gui colorscheme from the `UIEnter` event -- I think this is the nvim equivalent of gvim's .gvimrc file?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse this minimal.lua setup and first run `:TestBug1` to show how we failed to define MarkWord1. Then run `:TestBug2` to show that subsequent colorscheme invocations define MarkWord1.\n\nTested both with `nvim` and `neovide`.\n\n```lua\n-- Run this file as:\n--   nvim --clean -u minimal.lua\n--   neovide -- --clean -u minimal.lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"ColorScheme\" }, {\n    pattern = { \"*\" },\n    callback = function()\n      vim.cmd.highlight \"MarkWord1 ctermfg=0 ctermbg=14 guifg=Black guibg=#8ccbea\"\n      vim.cmd.echomsg \"'autocmd ColorScheme fired'\"\n    end,\n  })\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"UIEnter\" }, {\n    pattern = { \"*\" },\n    callback = function()\n      vim.cmd.colorscheme \"desert\"\n      vim.cmd.echomsg \"'autocmd UIEnter fired'\"\n    end,\n  })\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\"TestBug1\", function()\n  -- This should be defined, but it wasn't and errors.\n  vim.cmd.highlight \"MarkWord1\"\nend, {})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\"TestBug2\", function()\n  vim.cmd.colorscheme \"desert\"\n  -- It's defined this time.\n  vim.cmd.highlight \"MarkWord1\"\nend, {})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRegardless of where it's invoked, `:colorscheme` should fire the `ColorScheme` autocmd so long as the colorscheme is found.\n\nIn the test, `:TestBug1` should show a definition for MarkWord1 because that highlight should have been created after applying the colorscheme.\n\n\nSpecifically, I found that this prevents the [vim-mark](https://github.com/inkarkat/vim-mark) plugin from working.\nIt [listens to the ColorScheme](https://github.com/inkarkat/vim-mark/blob/157afc0149f14d8c3377414c3897ae5c5d466124/plugin/mark.vim#L117-L120) autocmd to create its highlights. Since setting my colorscheme does `:hi clear`, its initial marks are lost and they're never re-initialized since the autocmd doesn't fire. This plugin works correctly in gvim.\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.4 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1713484068\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, gvim 9.0.1576 (2022 Jun 28, compiled May 24 2023 22:48:17) MS-Windows 64-bit GUI version with OLE support\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nneovide and Windows Command Prompt\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop package manager",
